<paragraph id="0C5AE361FFA6FFBA15DBFA8FB589FAF2" blockId="13.[151,958,1263,1318]" box="[151,958,1294,1318]" pageId="13" pageNumber="238">
<treatmentCitationGroup id="2CF5C44FFFA6FFBA15DBFA8FB589FAF2" box="[151,958,1294,1318]" pageId="13" pageNumber="238">
<taxonomicName id="CBE598E2FFA6FFBA15DBFA8FB7D8FAF2" authority="(Distant)" baseAuthorityName="Distant" baseAuthorityYear="1918" box="[151,495,1294,1318]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Drabescus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="238" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigrofacialis">
<emphasis id="3E913F73FFA6FFBA15DBFA8FB7BCFAF2" box="[151,395,1294,1318]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="238">Drabescus nigrofacialis</emphasis>
(Distant)
</taxonomicName>
: 
<treatmentCitation id="8D44C570FFA6FFBA14B4FA8FB4C2FAF2" author="Zhang, Y. L. &amp; Webb, M. D." box="[504,757,1294,1318]" page="25" pageId="13" pageNumber="238" year="1996">
<bibRefCitation id="68749E90FFA6FFBA14B4FA8FB4C2FAF2" author="Zhang, Y. L. &amp; Webb, M. D." box="[504,757,1294,1318]" pageId="13" pageNumber="238" pagination="1 - 103" refId="ref11914" refString="Zhang, Y. L. &amp; Webb, M. D. (1996) A revised classification of the Asian and Pacific Selenocephalinae leafhoppers (Homoptera: Cicadellidae). Bulletin of the Natural History Museum, Entomology Series, 65, 1 - 103." type="journal article" year="1996">Zhang &amp; Webb 1996: 25</bibRefCitation>
</treatmentCitation>
, figs 327–332, 524.
</treatmentCitationGroup>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0C5AE361FFA6FFBA15DBFAD5B242F992" blockId="13.[151,1437,1364,2039]" pageId="13" pageNumber="238">Creamy white with rich and bold dark brown maculation on crown, pronotum and exposed mesonotum. Fore margin of head with transverse white band extending laterally onto greyish brown eyes. Face largely black, with areas on either side of frontal suture below eyes reddish dark brown. Antennae with flagellum ochraceous. Pronotum with median longitudinal stripe extending entire length, dark brown to black. Exposed mesonotum with basal triangles poorly developed, median area little darker with fewer white spots. Forewing hyaline with brownish tinge heavily spotted with dark brown except median transverse area, appendix dark brown, areas surrounding veins of apical cells dark brown; veins dark brown spotted with white. Thoracic pleurites and sternites dark brown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="44FFB0EAFFA6FFB9158BF9D1B42FFE95" lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="239" pageId="13" pageNumber="238" type="description">
<paragraph id="0C5AE361FFA6FFBA158BF9D1B2AAF92E" blockId="13.[151,1437,1364,2039]" pageId="13" pageNumber="238">Crown produced and triangular, medially longer than next to eyes, more or less flat, about 3× as wide between eyes as long medially, transition to face acutely angular, fore margin rimmed. Face with lateral frontal suture convex ventrad of antennal bases, distance between bases of antennae about 2.4× as wide as width of clypeus at apex; clypellus widened distally. Pronotum about 2.4× as wide as long medially, posterior margin concave. Exposed mesonotum longer than pronotum. Forewing claval veins connected by a cross vein. Fore tibia expanded.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0C5AE361FFA6FFBA158BF885B37BF822" blockId="13.[151,1437,1364,2039]" pageId="13" pageNumber="238">
<emphasis id="3E913F73FFA6FFBA158BF885B75DF8CA" box="[199,362,1796,1822]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="238">Male genitalia</emphasis>
. Pygofer broad basally and narrowed posteriorly, about 1.3× as long as height at base in lateral view, dorsal margin concave, dorsoposterior angle conically rounded with a spine-like process, sinuately curved and exceeding apex of pygofer. Valve with posterior margin medially emarginated, about 3.3× as wide as long medially. Subgenital plate elongate about 2.6× as long as wide at base, distal area narrowed into less sclerotized appendage. Style without subapical lobe, linear, apophysis widened before apex and narrowed apically, transversely striate. Connective with stem as long as arms. Aedeagus with dorsal apodeme well-developed, about half as long shaft; aedeagal shaft without basal processes, with lateral lamellate expansion in distal 0.33, gonopore subapical on ventral surface.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0C5AE361FFA5FFB9158BFF16B788FF01" blockId="14.[151,1437,151,898]" pageId="14" pageNumber="239">
<emphasis id="3E913F73FFA5FFB9158BFF16B7CFFF64" box="[199,504,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="239">Female pregenital segment</emphasis>
. Sternite VII 2.8× as wide as long, posterior margin produced medially with a median V-shaped excavation.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0C5AE361FFA5FFB9158BFF5EB42FFE95" blockId="14.[151,1437,151,898]" pageId="14" pageNumber="239">
<emphasis id="3E913F73FFA5FFB9158BFF5EB746FF2C" box="[199,369,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="239">Measurements.</emphasis>
Male 
<quantity id="CB1D4E84FFA5FFB914F7FF5EB47AFF2D" box="[443,589,223,249]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.35" metricValueMax="8.1" metricValueMin="6.6" pageId="14" pageNumber="239" unit="mm" value="7.35" valueMax="8.1" valueMin="6.6">6.6 –8.1 mm</quantity>
long, 2.6–3.0 mm wide across eyes and 
<quantity id="CB1D4E84FFA5FFB9116DFF5EB29DFF2D" box="[1057,1194,223,249]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.4" metricValueMax="2.6" metricValueMin="2.2" pageId="14" pageNumber="239" unit="mm" value="2.4" valueMax="2.6" valueMin="2.2">2.2–2.6 mm</quantity>
wide across posterolateral angles of pronotum. Female 
<quantity id="CB1D4E84FFA5FFB91760FE82B482FEC9" box="[556,693,259,285]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.3" metricValueMax="8.4" metricValueMin="8.2" pageId="14" pageNumber="239" unit="mm" value="8.3" valueMax="8.4" valueMin="8.2">8.2–8.4 mm</quantity>
long, 3.1–3.0 mm wide across eyes and 
<quantity id="CB1D4E84FFA5FFB911CBFE82B338FEC9" box="[1159,1295,259,285]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.65" metricValueMax="2.7" metricValueMin="2.6" pageId="14" pageNumber="239" unit="mm" value="2.65" valueMax="2.7" valueMin="2.6">2.6–2.7 mm</quantity>
wide across posterolateral angles of pronotum.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
